description:
This is simulated example data from the bboudata R package. It is intended to illustrate methods, and does not reflect reality for any particular boreal caribou population.

This text is included in the "data_description" tab of the survey data spreadsheet. See the example [here](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1i53nQrJXgrq3B6jO0ATHhSIbibtLq5TmmFL-PxGQNm8/edit?usp=sharing).

If you want to include formatted text in the description you need to use the Markdown language.  Below are some examples but see [here](https://www.markdownguide.org/cheat-sheet/) for more details about markdown.

Markdown formating can be used to **bold** or *italicize* text, create [links](www.google.com), or create lists:
  - Item 1
  - Item 2

And headings: 

#### Heading 1

##### Heading 2

Note in Google Sheets you can use Ctrl-Enter to add a new line.
